<HEADLINE>
<P>
250 ARRESTED AT ABORTION CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On June 16 The Times reported that detainees in the Chinese Changchun trials 
were "led into police stations in the painful posture called 'the airplane 
position' -- arms wrenched behind and in the air." 
</P>
<P>
On June 11, The Times reported that in Los Angeles each of a group of 
protesters refusing to comply with police orders to walk to a Los Angeles 
Police Department bus was approached by two officers who applied to that 
person's arms "a martial arts device composed of two pieces of wood connected 
with a chain or rope." As reported, torque applied to the device "often caused 
pain to show on the face of the person being arrested and sometimes a cry or a 
loud sob" (was heard). 
</P>
<P>
Aren't we in danger of being accused of living in a glass house when we 
criticize other countries for some of their behavior? 
</P>
<P>
LUCILLE K. FORER 
</P>
<P>
Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
