<HEADLINE>
<P>
REBUFFED SHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your front-page story from Miami Beach talking to the survivors of the "Voyage 
of the Damned" 50 years ago (June 5) was extremely powerful and moving in 
relating a very important episode in the Nazi Holocaust. 
</P>
<P>
To those of us who also survived this most tragic era in the history of 
mankind, it brought back painful memories of life in Nazi-occupied Europe, in 
constant fear of being caught and deported to the infamous death camps. 
</P>
<P>
Your staff writer, Barry Bearak, deserves great credit not only for having 
given such a detailed and faithful account of the sufferings of the Jewish 
people under Nazi domination, but also of their futile efforts to find refuge 
in the countries of the free world. 
</P>
<P>
Historian and Holocaust scholar David Wyman was right in stating that "if the 
world had opened its doors, hundreds of thousands of Jews would have been 
saved." 
</P>
<P>
Our sincere and deep appreciation to The Times for having devoted the space for 
this vital historic account. 
</P>
<P>
OTTO SCHIRN 
</P>
<P>
YVONNE SCHIRN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
