<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: TRACK STAR GLEN REYES SIGNS CONTRACT WITH ASTROS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glen Reyes, a four-time San Diego Section track champion from Orange Glen High, 
signed a professional baseball contract Tuesday night with the Houston Astros 
for an undisclosed amount. Reyes, drafted in the 13th round, will report to the 
Astros' Rookie League club in Kissimmee, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
Three other local players who were drafted in this month's amateur draft will 
attend college. Crawford High third baseman Manny Gagliano, drafted in the 17th 
round by Milwaukee, has signed a letter of intent to play baseball at Oklahoma 
State after turning down a $20,000 offer from the Brewers. 
</P>
<P>
"Three years of college should help a lot," Gagliano said. "My goal now is to 
become a No. 1 draft choice when I get out of college." 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel shortstop John Tejcek, selected in the 23rd round by Oakland, will 
play at the University of Arizona, which has won two NCAA baseball 
championships in the '80s. 
</P>
<P>
Miah Bradbury, who played at Mt. Carmel three years ago, turned down about 
$40,000 from the Philadelphia Phillies and will play his senior season at 
Loyola Marymount. Bradbury, a catcher, was taken by the Phillies in the sixth 
round. 
</P>
<P>
GOLF 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego Junior Golf Assn.'s Marvin K. Brown match-play championship 
begins today with the qualifying round for most divisions at the Torrey Pines 
Municipal Golf Course. The championship round for the 12-and-under division 
will be at the Sail Ho Golf Course at the U.S. Naval Training Center. For more 
information, call 280-8505. 
