<P>
MEETING TO DISCUSS TOXIC CLEANUP EFFORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County officials have set a public meeting Wednesday to explain 
their efforts to clean up contaminated soil and water at two plants operated by 
a defense contractor in the Santa Clarita Valley. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting comes in response to allegations that toxic chemicals illegally 
dumped by Space Ordnance Systems in Mint Canyon and Sand Canyon led to four 
cancer deaths in a single family. The meeting will be held at 4 p.m. in Santa 
Clarita City Hall, 23920 Valencia Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting will be members of a task force of citizens, health 
officials and company representatives organized after the contamination was 
discovered in 1984. Also attending will be members of a monitoring committee 
that has overseen cleanup efforts at the plants. 
</P>
