safety tests, becoming one of the first major cosmetics makers to do so. Animal 
rights activists praised Avon and said they hope its decision will encourage 
other companies to halt animal testing as a way of measuring a product's 
effectiveness and safety. The beauty products company said it will rely on 
alternative non-animal testing methods. 
