<P>
KURDS KILL 10 SOLDIERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DIYARBAKIR, Turkey 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ten Turkish soldiers were killed in a gunfight with separatist Kurdish 
guerrillas in rugged southeastern Turkey on Wednesday night, officials said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The clash, one of the biggest this year between Turkish forces and the Marxist 
Kurdish Workers Party, was near the hill town of Sirnak, 25 miles from the 
Iraqi border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
