<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NAVRATILOVA FIGHTS OFF FERNANDEZ TO ADVANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top-seeded Martina Navratilova overcame Mary Joe Fernandez, 7-6 (7-5), 6-1, 
Thursday in the quarterfinals of a women's grass-court tournament at 
Eastbourne, England. 
</P>
<P>
Joining Navratilova in the semifinals were 14th-seeded Raffaella Reggi of Italy 
and unseeded Gigi Fernandez of Puerto Rico and Ros Fairbank of South Africa. 
</P>
<P>
Reggi beat Akiko Kijimuta of Japan, 6-2, 4-6, 6-1; Fernandez beat Etsuko Inoue 
of Japan, 6-2, 6-4, and Fairbank defeated Betsy Nagelsen, 6-3, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Evert, who was forced to drop out of the Eastbourne tournament because of 
an ear infection, said she will make her 18th Wimbledon appearance when the 
grass-courts Grand Slam tournament begins next week. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm feeling much better," Evert said. "I shall be on medication for at least 
another three days, but I shall definitely be playing at Wimbledon next week." 
</P>
<P>
Michael Chang, the first American to win the French Open in 34 years, faces a 
tough test in his first match at Wimbledon. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Scanlon, a solid grass-court player but a qualifier this year, was placed 
against Chang, 17, who won at Roland Garros two weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan Shelton will face two-time champion Boris Becker, seeded third, and Scott 
Warner will face Miloslav Mecir of Czechoslovakia, seeded seventh, in other 
first-round draws. 
</P>
<P>
The top-seeded Becker defeated Italy's Diego Nargiso, 7-6 (7-3), 7-6 (7-5), to 
advance to the semifinals of a men's grass-court tournament at Wirral, England. 
</P>
<P>
Becker will play Dan Goldie in today's semifinals. Goldie beat Jeremy Bates of 
Britain, 7-5, 7-6 (10-8). 
</P>
<P>
The other semifinal pits Peter Lundgren of Sweden, a 6-4, 6-3, victor over Pete 
Sampras, against Carl-Uwe Steeb of West Germany, who beat Jim Pugh of Palos 
Verdes, 7-6 (7-5), 7-5. 
</P>
<P>
Michiel Schapers of the Netherlands upset top-seeded Derrick Rostagno of 
Brentwood, 6-4, 6-2, to reach the semifinals of a Grand Prix men's grass-court 
tournament at Bristol, England. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Matuszewski defeated Brad Drewett of Australia, 6-2, 7-6, to also 
advance. 
</P>
<P>
Others in today's semifinals are Eric Jelen of West Germany, who beat Kelly 
Evernden of New Zealand, 4-6, 6-4, 9-7, and Britain's Nick Brown, who won when 
West German opponent Michael Stich retired with a hamstring injury. Brown led 
at the time, 6-4, 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
Mats Wilander of Sweden beat Australian Darren Cahill, 3-6, 6-4, 6-4, in a 
grass-court exhibition tournament at Wentworth, England. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Curren overpowered Jonas Svensson of Sweden, 6-3, 6-3, in another match n 
the round-robin tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Claudio Mezzadri of Switzerland stunned top-seeded Javier Sanchez of Spain, 
6-4, 6-4, in the second round of the $125,000 Puglia tournament at Bari, Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
