<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Craft and Folk Art Museum will be moving down Wilshire Boulevard to take up 
rent-free residence at the May Co. while awaiting its new home in a multiuse 
complex to be built on the Miracle Mile. The museum will close at its present 
location next Friday, opening this fall at the nearby May Co. (at Wilshire 
Boulevard and Fairfax Avenue) where it will have about twice as much gallery 
space on the store's fourth floor, said museum director Patrick Ela. The new 
complex is scheduled to be completed in 1992. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
