<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORD OF MOUTH: WINE TASTING TO BENEFIT VILLA ESPERANZA, CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUTH REICHL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If you want to celebrate the start of summer, here's one nice way to do it. 
Saturday night from 7-9 the Urban Gourmet, 132 W. Colorado Blvd., Pasadena, 
will host a wine tasting with all the proceeds going to benefit Villa Esperanza 
and the Crippled Children's Society. 
</P>
<P>
Wines from Santa Ynez, Santa Barbara, Sanford, Gainey and Zaca Mesa wineries 
will be poured; an appetizer buffet is being cooked up by the Parkway Grill's 
Lorraine Oakley with desserts from Cafe Jacoulet's Ron Barbata and breads from 
the Old Town Bakery. 
</P>
<P>
The price is $25 per person. Reservations required: (818) 577-0100. RUTH REICHL 
</P>
